Python library to manage Daisy23-LCD + TouchButton Panel

2011 - Daniele Sdei, Marco Antonini

http://www.madefree.eu
http://wiki.madefree.eu
http://git.madefree.eu

Method:

mpr_init()
	Description

	MPR121 initialization.

	Syntax

	panel.mpr_init()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

mpr_irq()

	Description

	Returns True if electrode status changes, False otherwise.

	Syntax

	panel.mpr_irq()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

button_state()

	Description

	Returns the number of buttons pressed and a list of these.

Syntax

	panel.button_state()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

button_read()
	Description

	Returns a string that specifies the button pressed (Up, Down, Left, Right, Center).

	Syntax

	panel.button_read()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_lightOn()

	Description

	Turn the LCD backlight on.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_lightOn()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_lightOff()

	Description

	Turn the LCD backlight off.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_lightOff()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_setLight()

	Description

	Set the LCD backlight intensity.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_setLight(value)

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23
	value: an integer >=0 and <16

lcd_init()

	Description

	The initialization of LCD to default values.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_init()
	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_print()

	Description

	Prints text to the LCD

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_print(data)

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23
	data: the data to print

lcd_clear()

	Description

	Clears the LCD screen and positions the cursor in the upper-left corner.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_clear()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_home()

	Description

	Positions the cursor in the upper-left corner.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_home()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_setCursor()

	Description

	Position the LCD cursor

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_setCursor(col, row)

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23
	col: the column at which to position the cursor (with 0 being the first column)
	row: the row at which to position the cursor (with 0 being the first row)

lcd_display()

	Description

	Turns on the LCD display, after it's been turned off with lcd_noDisplay(). This will restore the text (and cursor) that was on the display.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_display()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_noDisplay()

	Description

	Turns off the LCD display, without losing the text currently shown on it.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_noDisplay()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_cursor()

	Description

	Display the LCD cursor: an underscore (line) at the position to which the next character will be written.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_cursor()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_noCursor()

	Description

	Hides the LCD cursor.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_noCursor()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_blink()

	Description

	Display the blinking LCD cursor.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_blink()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_noBlink()

	Description

	Turns off the blinking LCD cursor.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_noBlink()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_scrollDisplayLeft()

	Description

	Scrolls the contents of the display (text and cursor) one space to the left.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_scrollDisplayLeft()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_scrollDisplayRight()

	Description

	Scrolls the contents of the display (text and cursor) one space to the right.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_scrollDisplayRight()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_leftToRight()

	Description

	Set the direction for text written to the LCD to left-to-right, the default. This means that subsequent characters written to the display will go from left to right, but does not affect previously-output text.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_leftToRight()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_rightToLeft()

	Description

	Set the direction for text written to the LCD to right-to-left (the default is left-to-right). This means that subsequent characters written to the display will go from right to left, but does not affect previously-output text.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_rightToLeft()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_autoscroll()

	Description

	Turns on automatic scrolling of the LCD. This causes each character output to the display to push previous characters over by one space. If the current text direction is left-to-right (the default), the display scrolls to the left; if the current direction is right-to-left, the display scrolls to the right.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_autoscroll()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

lcd_noAutoscroll()

	Description

	Turns off automatic scrolling of the LCD.

	Syntax

	panel.lcd_noAutoscroll()

	Parameters

	panel: a variable of type Daisy23

